bamboo plant; bamboo didjeridoo; hollow stem of bamboo 1 to 1.5 m in length with narrow end as mouthpiece; moulded with bees-wax to required thick- ness to suit player; a kunbuk may be painted with designs  or left in its natural state; this versatile wind instrument  in the hands of an expert player  produces a variety of drones and imitative sounds; a difficult  circular breathing technique is necessary to maintain a continuous flow of air in the pipe; traditionally only males should use this artifact; women are prohibited from blowing one; any woman who broke this taboo would suffer the curse of barrenness.

pipe. Long cylinder sealed at each end with wax {(wom)} and with two holes in the upper side for smoking (with cigarette or bush tobacco or European tobacco).
